rbs-controller-class.summary: The ReadableByteStreamController interface of the Streams API represents a controller for a readable byte stream. ref-for-rs-get-reader⑤.name: getReader

ref-for-rs-locked②.name: locked

ref-for-rs-pipe-to④.name: pipeTo

rs-transfer.name: transferable
rs-transfer.summary: Transferable objects are objects that own resources that can be transferred from one context to another, ensuring that the resources are only available in one context at a time. rs-asynciterator.name: @@asyncIterator
rs-asynciterator.summary: The Symbol.asyncIterator static data property represents the well-known symbol @@asyncIterator. The async iterable protocol looks up this symbol for the method that returns the async iterator for an object. In order for an object to be async iterable, it must have an @@asyncIterator key.
rs-asynciterator.title: Symbol.asyncIterator

rs-class.name: ReadableStream

ref-for-generic-reader-cancel②.name: cancel

ref-for-generic-reader-cancel②.name: cancel

ref-for-generic-reader-closed②.name: closed

ref-for-generic-reader-closed②.name: closed
ref-for-generic-reader-closed②.summary: The closed read-only property of the ReadableStreamDefaultReader interface returns a Promise that fulfills when the stream closes, or rejects if the stream throws an error or the reader's lock is released. ref-for-byob-reader-read③.name: read
ref-for-byob-reader-read③.summary: The read() method of the ReadableStreamBYOBReader interface is used to read data into a view on a user-supplied buffer from an associated readable byte stream. A request for data will be satisfied from the stream's internal queues if there is any data present. If the stream queues are empty, the request may be supplied as a zero-copy transfer from the underlying byte source.

ref-for-byob-reader-release-lock②.name: releaseLock

byob-reader-class.name: ReadableStreamBYOBReader
byob-reader-class.summary: The ReadableStreamBYOBReader interface of the Streams API defines a reader for a ReadableStream that supports zero-copy reading from an underlying byte source. It is used for efficient copying from underlying sources where the data is delivered as an "anonymous" sequence of bytes, such as files.

notes: Must be imported using either require('stream/web') or import * from 'stream/web'.
Experimental implementation.

byob-reader-class.title: ReadableStreamBYOBReader

ref-for-rs-byob-request-respond①.name: respond

ref-for-default-writer-abort④.name: abort
ref-for-default-writer-abort④.summary: The abort() method of the WritableStreamDefaultWriter interface aborts the stream, signaling that the producer can no longer successfully write to the stream and it is to be immediately moved to an error state, with any queued writes discarded.
ref-for-default-writer-abort④.title: WritableStreamDefaultWriter: abort() method

ref-for-default-writer-close⑦.name: close
ref-for-default-writer-close⑦.summary: The close() method of the WritableStreamDefaultWriter interface closes the associated writable stream.
ref-for-default-writer-close⑦.title: WritableStreamDefaultWriter: close() method

ref-for-default-writer-closed②.name: closed
ref-for-default-writer-closed②.summary: The closed read-only property of the WritableStreamDefaultWriter interface returns a Promise that fulfills if the stream becomes closed, or rejects if the stream errors or the writer's lock is released.

ref-for-default-writer-desired-size⑥.name: desiredSize
ref-for-default-writer-desired-size⑥.summary: The desiredSize read-only property of the WritableStreamDefaultWriter interface returns the desired size required to fill the stream's internal queue.

Experimental implementation.
